Traffic Isolation and Filtering
To focus on the relevant laboratory data, the Display Filter was utilized to eliminate background noise from the host operating system.

Filter Applied: ip.addr == 192.168.1.192 was used to isolate all traffic originating from or destined for the Ubuntu VM.

Protocol Focus: The filter icmp was also applied to specifically monitor the Internet Control Message Protocol packets generated by the ping command.

Packet Data Interpretation
Based on the capture, the following communication pattern was established between the guest VM and the external gateway:

Sequence Validation: The analyzer captured a consistent pattern of Echo (ping) requests followed by Echo (ping) replies.

Addressing:

Source IP: 192.168.1.192 (The Ubuntu VM).

Destination IP: 142.251.41.174 (Google Server).

Layer 4 Details: Inspection of the ICMP header confirmed that requests were sent as Type 8 and replies were received as Type 0, verifying a healthy two-way connection.

